The paper discusses the security challenge of timing side-channels in cloud computing, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed solution involves provider-enforced deterministic execution, which relates to distributed computing (cs.DC) and parallel computing (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the implementation of a prototype OS, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.CR and cs.DC, followed by cs.SE, cs.Distributed, and cs.PL.
